Okay, but this is something that has really bothered me:
Both David Tennant and Michael Sheen are quite wrinkly (David when he...
body:
Okay, but this is something that has really bothered me:

Both David Tennant and Michael Sheen are quite wrinkly (David when he scrunches his forehead especially and Michael…. sort of just in general). Which is fine. But if Aziraphale and Crowley presented as women, that wouldn’t happen.

Im just saying, there’s a very real reason Frances McDormand is only ever heard and not seen, and why Frances McDormand in particular is only ever cast in very specific roles.

body:
Good Omens is pretty interesting

So Aziraphael and Crowley are in love. They are non binary but they both go with the male pronouns. They are asexuel and propably demiromantic (because they have romantic feeling for the SO).

How they spend thier time together is pretty cute. They go eating, enjoy thier time in some garden or they are in Azirapales bookstore.

I love the moments in the show where they have lunch. Aziraphale is always eating something while Crowley only orders himself coffee and decides to look at Aziraphale.

Mostly Crowley is the watcher in moments like these. It’s like his kind of happiness seeing Aziraphale happy. And that was I guess one of the reasons why he wanted to stop Armageddon.

I love the relationship between those two because it looks so human and cute. Both enjoy the small aspects of happiness.

Also I love thier characteristics:

-Crowley looks like a bad boy with the common behavior but he’s an angel in his heart. He never wanted to become a demon but he also would never fit in heaven because heaven is an awful conservative place. He’s soft, can’t say no to Aziraphale and kills only for self defence (kills Ligur before he had the chance to kill him) or protection (kills Nazis to save Aziraphale). He can’t think about a life without Aziraphale. That’s why he was in a point to give up when he thought his angel died. As he knew Aziraphale only lost his body and told him they would meet each other at the end of the world, Crowley had the energy to even go through fire to see his best friend again.

-Azirapale is a bit complicated. He wanted to be a good angel as possible but can’t fit in. He’s a book lover and a coward plus he’s in love with the enemy. That’s why he’s lying to the other angels. He became manipulative to cope with these problems. With Crowley he feels more save and confident because Crowley likes him for he really is not for he should be. The Angel struggels between heaven and his life in earth and that’s where the important part comes in. He should be a part of the army of angels, even in a high position but he said no and is ok with being called an coward and he started to think like a human would do. Making his own desicions.

In the end they prevented Armageddon and became thier own side. After they escaped thier punishment they are dinning at the Ritz and look each other.

They are in love, they are an old couple so they enjoy the small things in life.
